class loader and consider the JGroups Configurator for settings related to the key password. It looks like SYM_ENCRYPT doesn't have a keyPassword setter, which could complicate things. I need to ensure resource names aren't hardcoded and that I follow good coding practices with type annotations and public visibility. I'll also think about the implications of context class loaders in a native image. Writing a JCEKS file directly to resources might be a safer option.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring resource configurations**\\n\\nI'm considering that native-image resource configuration requires specific inclusions, and while the agent may catch changes, committing the binary could be fine. I wonder if generating a resource via keytool is an option. Ideally, it would be better to generate resources as Base64. The task relates to using getResourceAsStream, and I think a custom class loader is acceptable.\\n\\nHowever, I need to be careful with dynamic access since it targets ClassLoader#getResourceAsStream. If I override this, the resource access tracker might not recognize it. I need to verify that everything is covered and test the resource requests using an AtomicBoolean and resource name. I'll generate the keystore bytes with KeyGenerator, initializing with \\\"mykey\\\" in JCEKS format. Finally, I'll ensure I can assert the resource is correctly read and set the key.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating key generation options**\\n\\nI’m considering using SecureRandom for key generation in native environments, which could be a suitable choice. Perhaps I could use SecretKeySpec to address entropy issues since it seems deterministic. I should check if JCEKS can store SecretKeySpec, as it does implement SecretKey. If that’s the case, I might just create a new SecretKeySpec with a byte array for the key rather than using a KeyGenerator. This might simplify things significantly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_m14PN30BHCGFWebIba9hTXn6|fc_025e6aace4eb166f0169f27ccb8ebc8190aeff48533f7637ec", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jgroups/jgroups/5.2.0.Final/src/test/java/org_jgroups/jgroups/SYMENCRYPTTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_jgroups.jgroups;\n\nimport org.jgroups.protocols.SYM_ENCRYPT;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport javax.crypto.spec.SecretKeySpec;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.security.KeyStore;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class SYMENCRYPTTest {\n    private static final String KEYSTORE_RESOURCE = \"org_jgroups/jgroups/sym-encrypt-test.jceks\";\n    private static final String KEYSTORE_PASSWORD = \"changeit\";\n    private static final String KEY_ALIAS = \"mykey\";\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsSecretKeyFromContextClassLoaderResource() throws Exception {\n        byte[] keystoreContent = createKeyStoreContent();\n        ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        ResourceClassLoader resourceClassLoader = new ResourceClassLoader(\n            originalContextClassLoader,\n            KEYSTORE_RESOURCE,\n            keystoreContent);\n        SYM_ENCRYPT encryption = new SYM_ENCRYPT()\n            .keystoreName(KEYSTORE_RESOURCE)\n            .storePassword(KEYSTORE_PASSWORD)\n            .alias(KEY_ALIAS);\n\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(resourceClassLoader);\n\n            encryption.init();\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader);\n        }\n\n        assertThat(resourceClassLoader.requestedResource()).isEqualTo(KEYSTORE_RESOURCE);\n        assertThat(encryption.secretKey()).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(encryption.secretKey().getAlgorithm()).isEqualTo(\"AES\");\n        assertThat(encryption.symVersion()).isNotEmpty();\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] createKeyStoreContent() throws Exception {\n        KeyStore keyStore = KeyStore.getInstance(\"JCEKS\");\n        char[] password = KEYSTORE_PASSWORD.toCharArray();\n        SecretKeySpec secretKey = new SecretKeySpec(new byte[16], \"AES\");\n        KeyStore.SecretKeyEntry keyEntry = new KeyStore.SecretKeyEntry(secretKey);\n\n        keyStore.load(null, password);\n        keyStore.setEntry(KEY_ALIAS, keyEntry, new KeyStore.PasswordProtection(password));\n\n        ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        keyStore.store(outputStream, password);\n        return outputStream.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static final class ResourceClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final String resourceName;\n        private final byte[] resourceContent;\n        private final AtomicReference<String> requestedResource = new AtomicReference<>();\n\n        private ResourceClassLoader(ClassLoader parent, String resourceName, byte[] resourceContent) {\n            super(parent);\n            this.resourceName = resourceName;\n            this.resourceContent = resourceContent;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public InputStream getResourceAsStream(String name) {\n            requestedResource.set(name);\n            if (resourceName.equals(name)) {\n                return new ByteArrayInputStream(resourceContent);\n            }\n            return super.getResourceAsStream(name);\n        }\n\n        private String requestedResource() {\n            return requestedResource.get();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.jgroups/jgroups/5.2.0.Final/src/test/java/org_jgroups/jgroups/SYMENCRYPTTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_jgroups.jgroups;\\n\\nimport org.jgroups.protocols.SYM_ENCRYPT;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport javax.crypto.spec.SecretKeySpec;\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\\nimport java.io.InputStream;\\nimport java.security.KeyStore;\\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class SYMENCRYPTTest {\\n    private static final String KEYSTORE_RESOURCE = \\\"org_jgroups/jgroups/sym-encrypt-test.jceks\\\";\\n    private static final String KEYSTORE_PASSWORD = \\\"changeit\\\";\\n    private static final String KEY_ALIAS = \\\"mykey\\\";\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void loadsSecretKeyFromContextClassLoaderResource() throws Exception {\\n        byte[] keystoreContent = createKeyStoreContent();\\n        ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\\n        ResourceClassLoader resourceClassLoader = new ResourceClassLoader(\\n            originalContextClassLoader,\\n            KEYSTORE_RESOURCE,\\n            keystoreContent);\\n        SYM_ENCRYPT encryption = new SYM_ENCRYPT()\\n            .keystoreName(KEYSTORE_RESOURCE)\\n            .storePassword(KEYSTORE_PASSWORD)\\n            .alias(KEY_ALIAS);\\n\\n        try {\\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(resourceClassLoader);\\n\\n            encryption.init();\\n        } finally {\\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader);\\n        }\\n\\n        assertThat(resourceClassLoader.requestedResource()).isEqualTo(KEYSTORE_RESOURCE);\\n        assertThat(encryption.secretKey()).isNotNull();\\n        assertThat(encryption.secretKey().getAlgorithm()).isEqualTo(\\\"AES\\\");\\